contentrichtext.text: '''G0''', '''G<sup>0</sup>''', '''G<sub>0</sub>''', or '''g<sub>0</sub>''' may refer to: * [[G0 phase]] of cell division * '''G0 star''', a subclass of G-[[stellar classification|class stars]] * [[Ghana International Airlines]] IATA airline designator * [[Ground zero]], sometimes used as an abbreviation to refer to the World Trade Center site of the 9/11 attacks * [[Group 0]], an alternate name for Group 18 of the Periodic table – the Noble gases ** a hypothetical group in the Periodic table, which would consist of [[neutronium]] * [[Geometric continuity]], notated G<sup>0</sup> * [[Standard gravity]], notated g<sub>0</sub> * [[Conductance quantum|Quantum of conductance]], notated G<sub>0</sub> * [[G-Zero world]] – the term used for the emerging [[power vacuum|vacuum]] in international politics in the early 21st Century. ==See also== * [[0G (disambiguation)]] * [[GO (disambiguation)]] {{Letter-Number Combination Disambiguation}}
